The paper deals with deep neural network architectures and their training, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on initialization techniques and regularization, which are important topics in the subfield of deep learning (cs.LG). The experiments are conducted on image classification (cs.CV) and machine translation, which are common applications of deep learning. The paper also discusses the exploding and vanishing gradient problem, which is a common issue in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of regularization techniques, which is a common topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning in general (cs.AI).
